                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_aǧ0yjyn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>aǧ˳yjyn</orth><form type="participle"><orth>aǧ˳yd</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>aǧujun</orth><form type="participle"><orth> aǧud</orth></form></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>повадиться</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>get the habit</q></tr></sense><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>капризничать</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>be capricious</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>беситься</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>madden</q></tr></sense></sense><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>aǧ˳yd</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>aǧud</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>бешеный</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>mad</q></tr></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>īw bīræǧ næ fosyl saǧ˳ydi</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>один волк повадился (ходить) к нашему стаду</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>one wolf got into the habit of (walking) to our herd</q></tr></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>zærbatgutæ isaǧudæncæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ласточки пришли в смятение</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the swallows got mad</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 13</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>aǧ˳yd kujtaw mæm læbūrync</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>они кидаются на меня, как бешеные собаки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they rush at me like mad dogs</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Niger"/><biblScope>134</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>aǧud beræǧtaw</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>как бешеные волки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>like mad wolves</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>286%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>dengiz aǧudaw læburdta nawtæmæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>море, как бешеное, кидалось на корабли</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the sea, as if it was mad, threw itself on the ships</q></tr><bibl><biblScope>Geografi I 62</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>aǧud kuji komi finkæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пена изо рта бешеной собаки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>foam from the mouth of a mad dog</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1936 I 67</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>īw bīræǧ næ fosyl saǧ˳ydi</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>один волк повадился (ходить) к нашему стаду</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>one wolf got into the habit of (walking) to our herd</q></tr></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>zærbatgutæ isaǧudæncæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ласточки пришли в смятение</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the swallows got mad</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 13</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>aǧ˳yd kujtaw mæm læbūrync</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>они кидаются на меня, как бешеные собаки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they rush at me like mad dogs</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Niger"/><biblScope>134</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>aǧud beræǧtaw</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>как бешеные волки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>like mad wolves</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>286%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>dengiz aǧudaw læburdta nawtæmæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>море, как бешеное, кидалось на корабли</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the sea, as if it was mad, threw itself on the ships</q></tr><bibl><biblScope>Geografi I 62</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>aǧud kuji komi finkæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пена изо рта бешеной собаки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>foam from the mouth of a mad dog</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1936 I 67</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Корень *%igu-%i, сращенный с превербом %ia-%i; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>gū(jū-, zū-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>gū-(jū-)</w> <gloss><q>идти</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>спешить</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><author>А. Fгеimаn</author><biblScope>Rocznik Orjentalistyczny, 3, 1927, стр. 161</biblScope></bibl>).%r1%r Осетинский отражает здесь старую непалатали зованную форму %igu-%i, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>-gu</w></mentioned> во второй части сложных слов: <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>vanar-gu</w> <gloss><q>бродящий по лесу</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>agre-gu</w> <gloss><q>идущий в голове</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и т. п. Та же основа, сращенная с превербом %iīv%i | %iev%i-, налична еще в одном осетинском глаголе: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īvǧ0yjyn"/> I %ievǧujun%i ‘миновать’ q. v. Сюда же <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zyd"/> | %izud%i ‘жадный’.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The root *%igu-%i combined with the preverb %ia-%i; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>gū(jū-, zū-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>gū-(jū-)</w> <gloss><q>go</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>hurry</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><author>А. Fгеimаn</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Rocznik Orjentalistyczny, 3, 1927, стр. 161</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Rocznik Orjentalistyczny, 3, 1927, p. 161</biblScope></bibl>).%r1%r Ossetic displays here an old unpalatalized form %igu-%i, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>-gu</w></mentioned> in the second part of compounds: <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>vanar-gu</w> <gloss><q>wandering through the woods</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>agre-gu</w> <gloss><q>going ahead</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc. The same stem combined with the preverb %iīv%i | %iev%i- is found in another one Ossetic verb: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īvǧ0yjyn"/> I %ievǧujun%i ‘escape’ q. v. Also see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zyd"/> | %izud%i ‘greedy’.</etym><note type="footnote" xml:lang="ru" n="1">Сопоставление с <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>%r3%r gav</w> <gloss><q>кричащий</q></gloss></mentioned> менее убедительно, ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īvǧ0yjyn"/>.</note><note type="footnote" xml:lang="en" n="1">The comparison with <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>%r3%r gav</w> <gloss><q>crying</q></gloss></mentioned> is less convincing, cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īvǧ0yjyn"/>.</note></entry></body></text></TEI>